# Orchestrator Agent Rules

## Project Structure

```
server.py                  # Backend: FastAPI + WebSocket + Gemini Live
memory_video.py            # Google API: stylize + Veo pipeline
storybook_generator.py     # Google API: Gemini interleaved storybook
billing_monitor.py         # Cost tracking
static/
  index.html               # Frontend: landing page
  participant.html          # Frontend: call UI (book-themed)
  memories.html             # Frontend: post-call memorabilia
AGENTS.md                  # Agent roles and contracts
skills.md                  # Implementation-level API reference
```

## Integration Contract

WebSocket messages use `type` field. Adding a new message type requires updating:
1. Server send logic in `server.py`
2. `handleMessage()` switch in `participant.html`
3. Message types table in `AGENTS.md`

## Cost Discipline

- Every API call must go through `log_api_call()` with realistic cost
- Billing UI polls at 15s intervals (not faster)
- Audio input logging batches to ~30s
- Vision captions only on key moments (>50% label change + 8s debounce)
- Total budget: $25 for the hackathon

## Deployment

- Cloud Run with `--session-affinity` for WebSocket support
- Health check: `GET /health` → `{"status": "ok"}`
- Readiness: `GET /ready` → system status with API availability
- Static files mounted last: `app.mount("/static", ...)`

## Parallelism Rules

- Audio is the critical path — NEVER gate it behind a semaphore
- Vision API (`batch_annotate_images`) is synchronous gRPC — ALWAYS run via `asyncio.to_thread()`
- All Gemini calls (except Live audio) go through `_gemini_sem` (Semaphore=4)
- All Vision calls go through `_vision_sem` (Semaphore=3)
- State mutations (appending to screenshots/captions/etc.) go through `room._state_lock`
- Post-call generation uses background tasks with `_generation_tasks` dict for status polling
- Frontend polls `/generation-status/{task_id}` and renders each result as it arrives

## Error Philosophy

API failures are expected. Audio translation is critical path (must not crash). Vision, narration, storybook, and video are best-effort (log errors, continue).
